  "market_context": "Crude oil daily chart spanning multiple months, showing alternating swings between roughly 55.00 and 65.00, with prior monthly highs near 62.50 and monthly lows near 55.50. Used as a teaching example for marking relevant swing points.",
  "key_observation": "Relevant highs and lows on the daily chart are those that align with higher-time-frame (monthly) swings and have meaningful separation from adjacent swings; the analyst uses a fixed three-higher-time-frame-candle look-back to qualify them.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identify a relevant low on the daily chart, justified by significant separation from the previous low, making it a valid location for a reversal.",
    "Step 2: Confirm the relevant low and a subsequent relevant high coincide with monthly highs/lows, classifying them as higher-time-frame levels.",
    "Step 3: Apply the fractal model indicator and focus only on relevant highs/lows that also represent higher-time-frame swing points.",
    "Step 4: Define the look-back as three higher-time-frame candles — on the daily chart this means three months back (1, 2, 3 months).",
    "Step 5: Demonstrate fractality: on the hourly chart the look-back becomes three days, preserving the same logic across time frames.",
    "Step 6: Practice on a final example by marking equal highs / failure swings as the relevant high, and assessing lows by separation to determine which qualifies as relevant."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "Only swing points that align with higher-time-frame structure and sit within the last three HTF candles should be considered relevant; these provide the best reactions and are the only valid locations to deploy the fractal model.",
